But they are stationed in areas where there is only a minimum of violence and the fighting requirements for them are not as high as for us in the southern and eastern parts of the country," Gates said.
The British newspaper "Sun" described this week the German soldiers as lazy.
"Afghan non-Stuer uncovered: the Germans are playing games while our boys are fighting," the Sun wrote in a post supplemented by photos of German soldiers playing table tennis.
