Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which, in turn, depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the driver’s license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right car model.
First, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to provide the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of a damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the driver’s license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in case of a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be due.
This is why both people over 25 and women have to make fewer contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower rate of accidents thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, as they, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the company’s conviction, tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting out the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that most likely meets his personal needs.
We now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance in order to be able to make a choice not only in terms of performance but also in terms of price.
Those under the age of 25 encounter numerous obstacles when choosing an affordable insurance, such as the low driving practice and the “young” driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to make a full cascade insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full casco with self-contribution, so that while the benefits of a full casco insurance are covered, they are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay a part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
“The amount will be determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid,” explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europe, an online insurance broker.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage incurred on the own car.
Additionally, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here is a advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to reduce insurance costs; so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment implies an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and fines depends on the company and its revenues.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments,” Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract.The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Therefore, it is most reasonable to opt for a full-cash insurance with self-participation.
“Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving,” explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the “fear of the beginner” has been removed.
Nevertheless, for a married client who does not have children, it is more advisable to make a full-cash insurance; of course only if the financial situation of the person permits.
On the insurer’s side, couples with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are also low.
In this case, a full cash insurance with self-contribution (at an amount around 300 euros) would be the best option.In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which only applies to the third year of the vehicle.
“They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make higher contributions,” notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to enter into a full cash insurance with self-investment (at an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, one must note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accidental damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough choice that fits our personal situation.
