They can even be advantageous for card issuers.
The incentives for consumers to continue to pay mortgage rates decrease when the property is less valuable than the value of the loan; as a result, card debt becomes more important among repayment priorities.
Card issuers can also react to the more stormy conditions much faster and more flexibly than lenders by changing interest rates or credit limits.
